There are currently about 18,000 of these machines in the United States and Abbott hopes to increase production to provide 50,000 tests per day. A test that uses a monoclonal antibody and the particular link to the protein of the nucleocapidium (protein N) of the new coronavirus is being developed in Taiwan, with the expectation of delivering results in 15 to 20 minutes such as a rapid flu test.
A literature review in March 2020 concluded that "Torax radiographs have a lower diagnostic value in the initial stages, while TC findings, computerized tomography, may be present even before symptoms occur."
