If a person becomes ill on a plane, appropriate controls to protect workers and other passengers include the isolation of the patient from the other person for a distance of 6 feet, with the appointment of a crew member to serve the patient and offer her a facial mask, or ask the patient to cover the mouth and nose with lenses when coughing or breathing.
