Work in high exposure necroteriums includes workers involved in the preparation of bodies of people with confirmed COPID-19 or suspected of disease at the time of their death; the risk of exposure becomes very high if they perform autopsy. Additional engineering controls for these risk groups include isolation rooms for patients with confirmed COPID-19 or suspected of disease, including when aerosol generator procedures are performed.
