There are three vaccination strategies being investigated.
First, researchers aim to develop a vaccine with the comprehensive virus.
The use of this virus, whether it is inactive or dead, aims to cause a rapid immunological response of the human body to a new infection of COVID-19.
A second strategy, subunitary vaccines, aims to create a vaccine that sensitizes the immune system to certain subunits of the virus.
In the case of SARS-CoV-2, this research focuses on the protein of the mirror that helps the virus enter the enzyme ACE2 receptor.
A third strategy is that of nucleic acid vaccines (DNA or RNA vaccines, a new technique for creating vaccines).
Experimental vaccines of any of these strategies should have the safety and efficacy tested. On 16 March 2020, the first clinical test of a vaccine began with four volunteers in Seattle.
